  <entry>
    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/13148</id>
    <published>2012-08-30T00:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2012-08-30T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/driver-and-rider-tests-and-instructor-statistics-quarter-1-2012-13"/>
    <title>Driver and rider tests and instructor statistics: quarter 1 2012/13</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;This publication presents information on the number and pass rates of driving and riding tests conducted in Great Britain to 31st June 2012 (beginning of the 2012/13 financial year).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The statistics are derived from data held by the Driving Standards Agency (DSA), which administers the driving test and training schemes in Great Britain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="key-points"&gt;Key points&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A total of 410,778 tests were conducted across all test categories between April and June 2012 (Q1 2012/13). This is a decrease of 4.9 per cent in comparison with the same quarter in 2011/12.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The reduction in the number of tests conducted in quarter 1 2012/13 is likely to have been due to the continuing economic situation and the Jubilee long weekend at the beginning of June 2012.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The practical car test pass rate was unchanged from quarter 1 2011/12, at 47 per cent.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;At the end of the quarter there were 46,313 approved driving instructors on the Register.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;h2 id="technical-information"&gt;Technical information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Information on Driver and Rider Test and Instructor statistics, including the pre-release access list, and related technical documentation &lt;a href="https://whitehall-admin.production.alphagov.co.uk/technical-guidance-for-transport-stats?&amp;amp;preview=8996#driving-tests-and-instructors-statistics"&gt;can be found here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

